Method Detail

act

public void act(Client controller)
Description copied from interface: Actor
Do the work here. Actors should be reasonably atomic and do a single piece of work. They should support the repeat count and the inter request delay, but they may choose not to for purposes of being bad actors to test the framework. It's also possible to write an actor that does one request and returns. The ActionThread now loops, so multiple actors can be strung together in an ActorChain, providing the ability to progress through a complex transaction, without having to do it inside a single act method. This should help writing more, simpler Actors.

Parameters:
controller - StandalonePingReceiveUpdatesClient object for resources.
